webpackJsonp([64740889324736],{326:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/benjaminmodayil/Documents/sites/modayilme_gatsby/src/pages/posts/blog/02-21-2018-rad-resources/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>Hey there! I sure love me some neat web tools/resources. There always seem to be new ones released every week. I decided to list some of my favorite random resources below for DEV/DES/ETC.</p>\n<h2><strong>Presentation-Related</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://carbon.now.sh">Carbon</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Fonts</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://archetypeapp.com/#">Arch</a><a href="">e</a><a href="https://archetypeapp.com/#">type</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Colors</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://coolors.co/">Coolors</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.grabient.com/">Grabient</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://gradiblock.com/">Gradiblock</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Shadows</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.cssmatic.com/box-shadow">Box-Shadows Generator</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://css3gen.com/text-shadow/">Text shadows</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://codepen.io/sdthornton/pen/wBZdXq">Material Shadows</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Illustrations</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://undraw.co/illustrations">Undraw Illustrations</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>SVG</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://qrohlf.com/trianglify/">Triangle pattern generator</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.svgrepo.com/">SVG-REPO</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.heroicons.com/">SVG Icons</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://jakearchibald.github.io/svgomg/">Compressor</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.heropatterns.com/">Hero Patterns</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.svgbackgrounds.com/">SVG Backgrounds</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Placeholders</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://via.placeholder.com/350x150">Placeholder.it</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.fillmurray.com/">Fillmurray</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://picsum.photos/">Picsum</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Reference</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://sdras.github.io/array-explorer/">Array Explorer</a> by Sarah Drasner</li>\n<li><a href="https://surma.github.io/underdash/">Array Manipulation Copy/Paste</a> by Surma</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Utility</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://hreftools.com/">https://hreftools.com/</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Meta</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://megatags.co/#generate-tags">MetaTag Generator</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.heymeta.com/url/www.modayil.me">Hey Meta</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Utility CSS Libraries</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">TailwindCSS</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://tachyons.io/#principles">Tachyons</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Inspiration</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://gangbase.design/">Gangbase</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.creative-portfolios.com/">Creative Portfolios</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://bestfolios.com/">More portfolios</a></li>\n<li>Nice <a href="http://heynishi.com/">copywriting</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Do you have any rad resources youâ€™d like to share? Send me a message on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/modayilme">@modayil.me</a> Rad resources only, please ğŸ™.</p>',frontmatter:{date:"21 February, 2018",title:"ğŸ”¥ Rad Resources ğŸ’¯",tldr:"Random neato resources for your next project.",path:"/blog/rad-resources"}}},pathContext:{path:"/blog/rad-resources",prev:{html:'<p>Hey friends reading this! Albeit my Google Analytics will say is nobodyâ€¦ This is the first of many update logs.</p>\n<p>Here, Iâ€™ll try providing information on my current status. This could entail professional and personal updates, or whatever constitutes sharing. The goal of these update logs is to journalize thoughts, learnings, musings as I become a full-stack developer, and even beyond, but without going into detail as a normal topical blog post. So in a sense, these could be thought of like â€œshow-notesâ€ that you might see on a particular podcast episode <em>cue Truman show vibe</em> (also comparable to a â€œstand upâ€).</p>\n<p>This first one will be pretty long though, just because itâ€™s collecting what Iâ€™ve been doing since my apprenticeship.</p>\n<h2>Update from November 26th to January 31st</h2>\n<h3>Professional Updates</h3>\n<h4>Wordpress</h4>\n<p>Iâ€™ve been doing quite a bit with learning Wordpress and its ecosystem, but Iâ€™m a little stopped on a learning project with Wordpress as Iâ€™m taking classes for fullstack development at the moment. I decided to learn Wordpress as itâ€™s the CMS that tends to be in demand with digital agencies/ or freelance projects. As Iâ€™m coming from <a href="craftcms.com">CraftCMS</a> (a superior CMS if you asked me), Iâ€™ve been using <a href="advancedcustomfields.com">ACF</a> (Advanced Custom Fields) plugin to create sites in a similar fashion. I havenâ€™t dug too much into Wordpressâ€™s new (beta) Gutenberg editor, so Iâ€™m hoping it leads to an easier development process whenever I get back to Wordpress Development.</p>\n<h4>Readings</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Accessibility for Everyone</strong> by <em>Laura Kalbag</em>: Gave a good general overview of what to use on the web when it comes to accessiblity. Abookapart books tend to lack in depth, but still gives you general directions when youâ€™re mad googling.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>The New CSS Layout</strong> by <em>Rachel Andrew</em>: Learned a lot about CSS Grid and some flexbox techniques I never knew before.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Atomic Design</strong> by <em>Brad Frost</em>: Design systems are a little out of my wheelhouse, but Brad Frostâ€™s book was a great overview into his coined methodology.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>CSS Grid</h4>\n<p>Wes Bos recently launched his <a href="cssgrid.io">CSS Grid course</a> and I was lucky to get onto the beta. Itâ€™s a short and practical course for deepdiving into it. I actually got to use it on an learning API project (linked below).</p>\n<h4>Email Newsletters</h4>\n<p>Iâ€™ve seen enough code for newsletters to know that I hate it. Iâ€™ve also heard countless people on the internet complain about email development that I decided to take another path. Enter <a href="mjml.io">MJML</a>. Itâ€™s a email framework that translates its proprietory tags into email compliant code. Hereâ€™s an <a href="https://codepen.io/modayilme/pen/RxPBdb">example newsletter</a> showing the code it exports. I have a blog post in the works for this one.</p>\n<h4>Personal Site development</h4>\n<p>I love <a href="gatsbyjs.org">GatsbyJS</a> more and more whenever working with it. Here are some updates Iâ€™ve been completed the past month or so:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Refreshed this siteâ€™s codebase into shorter components.</li>\n<li>Figured out how to use an API in React all by myself with a Codepen feed on the homepage.</li>\n<li>Solved my GroundRules SVG animation issue with a SVG handler for React (<a href="https://github.com/gilbarbara/react-inlinesvg">Github link</a>)</li>\n<li>Got my site to a 99% on page speed insights and fixed some accessibility issues detected by AXE</li>\n</ul>\n<p> Iâ€™m currently working on a Wordpress API integration, but Iâ€™m holding out until Gutenberg becomes more stable, just in case I have to update the integration again.</p>\n<h4>Fullstack Learning</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Finishing an API project using <a href="https://newsapi.org/">News API</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>View my progress here: Link to <a href="https://github.com/benjaminmodayil/API-Capstone">Github repo</a> and <a href="https://benjaminmodayil.github.io/API-Capstone/">demo site</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Progressing through Node development</li>\n<li>covered creating/reading/updating/destroying data with REST API endpoints</li>\n<li>currently learning testing with mocha and chai.</li>\n<li>almost ready for my second capstone project (3 total) and on track to graduate wwaaay early (because of prior experience).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Personal Updates</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Had a nice family trip to India (<a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/BcTEyWlgwHNIQ_Slmhhzktdu5osGaKRSeE8nLs0/?taken-by=modayilme">pictures</a>)</li>\n<li>Trying to blog more as a way to contemplate ideas deeper.</li>\n<li>Going for my permit soon and hopefully Iâ€™ll actually get practice behind a wheel so I can get my license ASAP.</li>\n<li>Trying to eat healthy again. I donâ€™t get much exercise anymore, so I need to adjust the scales somehow. Pun intended.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Requests</h2>\n<p>Prayer. Need lots of it. ğŸ™</p>\n<p>End of update ğŸ‘‹</p>',id:"/Users/benjaminmodayil/Documents/sites/modayilme_gatsby/src/pages/posts/blog/01-31-2018-update-log-001/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",frontmatter:{layout:"blog",title:"Update Log 001 ğŸ“‚",tldr:"Ben does a stand up.",path:"/blog/updatelog/001",type:"blog",external:null}},next:null}}}});
